cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation using fully convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new architecture for the network, which involves object boundary information and mask-level object proposals, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of relabeled boundaries suggests a machine learning approach (cs.LG), and the end-to-end trainable system implies the use of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments involve the PASCAL VOC segmentation benchmark, which is a common dataset in multimedia (cs.MM).
